{
  "messages": [
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "What should I work on next?"
        }
      ],
      "id": "S2wt1XB9vgECUIAB",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "cSit28j1vkfGCTZV",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": []
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "What should I work on next?"
        }
      ],
      "id": "Kt4c7EkxcywIeKyH",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "u8ajuTtZD8gnUFi9",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "oh, good question!\n---\nit looks like we've got the basic project set up, which is purr-fect! but all our core docs are empty still.\n---\nso, the very first thing we usually nail down is the project's vision. like, what's the big idea here?\n---\nwhat's the one thing you're trying to achieve with this app?\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "b6FPJRQlNWu0xtcs",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "tell me about the vision",
              "what's the app for?",
              "let's talk features first"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "tell me about the vision",
              "what's the app for?",
              "let's talk features first"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "I'm trying to build a tasks app for doctors "
        }
      ],
      "id": "Rwp6EaNoQiNsC5L4",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "rsZyFurOu9p0Gibf",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aha, a tasks app for doctors! that's a super clear direction.\n---\nis it for managing their *own* tasks, or tasks *for patients* from their team, or something else entirely?\n---\nknowing that will help me start fleshing out the vision spec!\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "sNS8vwthQBnmUSpP",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "tasks for patients",
              "tasks for themselves",
              "both"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "tasks for patients",
              "tasks for themselves",
              "both"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "both"
        }
      ],
      "id": "68ASkuccXpjlnASw",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "48MhdwOE5RWcKQFL",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "both, got it! that makes a lot of sense for a doctor's workflow.\n---\nso, to make sure I capture this vision perfectly, what's the ultimate goal here? like, what problem does this app solve for them, and what does success look like for a doctor using it?\n\n",
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "D1LQDvXsDVm7cyEi",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "what problem does it solve?",
              "what does success look like?",
              "let's dive into features"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "what problem does it solve?",
              "what does success look like?",
              "let's dive into features"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "I want a simple kanband board like trello"
        }
      ],
      "id": "0WOZuCSNdumWtvWO",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "kueVNSv8nMR1JIUx",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "oh, a kanban board! like trello, but for doctors. i love that for task management.\n---\nso, are the columns fixed (like \"to-do,\" \"in progress,\" \"done\") or can doctors customize them for their different workflows?\n---\ni'd lean towards customisable columns to give them more flexibility, what do you think?\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "WFjLwf3MLiFkrm8D",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "customizable columns",
              "fixed columns for now",
              "you decide, Flexi"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "customizable columns",
              "fixed columns for now",
              "you decide, Flexi"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Umm, so each patient is a card right....you decide "
        }
      ],
      "id": "D9UYczt3GZQXwn5q",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "sNzeoZyrMLp2Ahjb",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "okay, each patient is a card — got it, that's a super clear way to connect tasks to the actual people!\n---\nand for the columns, i'm going to say **customizable**. this gives doctors the flexibility to set up boards for different patient groups or even different stages of care, which feels much more powerful.\n---\nso, this means we'll need a way for them to add, rename, and reorder those columns.\n---\nnow, thinking about this kanban board, what's the most important *action* a doctor will take with those patient cards? like, what's the core interaction that makes this app valuable for them?\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "xptww3xWxv39E5wW",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "moving cards between columns",
              "adding new patient cards",
              "assigning tasks on cards"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "moving cards between columns",
              "adding new patient cards",
              "assigning tasks on cards"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Voice not updates , one click approvals confirmations of status, requests etc"
        }
      ],
      "id": "1z0FwvIZ24YlsilH",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "OENoZpSF1AzEfjcO",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "voice notes, one-click approvals, confirmations, requests... wow, that's a lot of powerful interactions packed into those cards!\n---\ni'm imagining a doctor just tapping a button or speaking a quick update, and boom, it's done. very efficient.\n---\nso, for these actions, are we mostly talking about updating the *patient's status* on their card, or are there also specific *tasks within* each patient card that get approved or confirmed?\n---\nit'll help me figure out the data model for those patient cards!\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "v0ds3Al0XlJmGvqK",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "updating patient status",
              "approving tasks within a card",
              "both are important"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "updating patient status",
              "approving tasks within a card",
              "both are important"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "both are important"
        }
      ],
      "id": "g3xfrwAaLen83Na5",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "ut304gsSkPvlB3vM",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "got it, both are important! so patient cards will have a main status, and then individual tasks within those cards will also have their own statuses that can be approved or confirmed.\n---\nthat's a really comprehensive way to manage patient care!\n---\nnow, when it comes to those tasks *within* a patient card, are these tasks usually assigned to other team members (like nurses or assistants), or are they mostly for the doctor's own to-do list?\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "YQ6ns2BPJDcuOZ8C",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "assigned to team members",
              "for the doctor's own list",
              "both, depending on the task"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "assigned to team members",
              "for the doctor's own list",
              "both, depending on the task"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "both, depending on the task"
        }
      ],
      "id": "wTWjhDqFi24u5OBU",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "vboI4LVJVmq2HnaL",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "okay, both, depending on the task — that makes total sense! so sometimes it's \"i need to review this lab result,\" and other times it's \"nurse flexi needs to call this patient.\"\n---\nthis means we'll definitely need a way to assign tasks to different team members, and maybe even show who's responsible for what on the card itself.\n---\nis task assignment and collaboration a top-tier \"must-have\" feature, or something we can add in a later version?\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "Uu305Chy2n6OSnJF",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "must-have for version one",
              "nice-to-have later",
              "let's talk about something else"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "must-have for version one",
              "nice-to-have later",
              "let's talk about something else"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "I think people are assigned to patients rather than individual tasks mostly, then all tasks assigned to that patient flow to them "
        }
      ],
      "id": "u1jeXQAwTwhqLnsb",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "lCw8XrzGXPKgMKhY",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ah, that's a super important clarification! so it's patient-centric assignment, not task-centric. i like that — it simplifies things a lot for creating tasks.\n---\nso, a team member (like a doctor or nurse) is assigned to a *patient*, and then any tasks for that patient automatically show up in *their* task list.\n---\nthat means when a team member looks at their \"my tasks\" view, they're seeing all tasks across all patients they're assigned to.\n---\nis there a scenario where multiple team members might be assigned to a *single patient*? or is it usually one primary person per patient?\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "K61WvNUkqmeS4foz",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "one primary person per patient",
              "multiple team members per patient",
              "what about different roles?"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "one primary person per patient",
              "multiple team members per patient",
              "what about different roles?"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "There will be hangovers depending on shift and specialists orderlies, doctors junior doctors etc "
        }
      ],
      "id": "D8zxYhzi9pZCEsnw",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "iyYRvisbrd7GAvk9",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "okay, \"hangovers\" and multiple roles — specialists, orderlies, junior doctors, oh my! that paints a picture of a dynamic team.\n---\nso, a patient might have a primary doctor, a specialist, and a junior doctor assigned to them, and these assignments could even change with shifts. that's a lot of moving parts.\n---\nfor our first version, do we need to track the *history* of who was assigned when (for handovers and audit trails), or is it enough to just know who the *currently active* team members for a patient are?\n---\ntracking the current team is simpler to start, but i want to make sure we don't miss anything critical for those handovers!\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "oehq5QGjfvvAmmYP",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "just the current team for now",
              "we need historical assignments",
              "how would handovers work then?"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "just the current team for now",
              "we need historical assignments",
              "how would handovers work then?"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Handovers* my bad haha"
        }
      ],
      "id": "BuqQO6jyVnNCXK9n",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "PlUleQx4sN9HTq2J",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "haha, no worries, \"handovers\" makes much more sense in a medical context than \"hangovers\" for sure! my feline brain was trying to figure out how to track that! 😹\n---\nso, back to those handovers — do we need to track the *history* of who was assigned to a patient and when (for that full audit trail), or is it enough to just know who the *currently active* team members for a patient are for the first version?\n---\nknowing the current team is simpler to start, but i want to make sure we get those handovers right.\n\n",
          "providerMetadata": {
            "google": {
              "thoughtSignature": ""
            }
          },
          "state": "done"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool-suggest",
          "toolCallId": "PgcufF9OtYUCVYUs",
          "state": "output-available",
          "input": {
            "suggestions": [
              "just the current team for now",
              "we need historical assignments",
              "how would handovers work then?"
            ]
          },
          "output": {
            "suggestions": [
              "just the current team for now",
              "we need historical assignments",
              "how would handovers work then?"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "just the current team for now"
        }
      ],
      "id": "MK4nhfCnL6fAJFzi",
      "role": "user"
    },
    {
      "id": "zZ1Z9oVBLHYusIfK",
      "role": "assistant",
      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "step-start"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "purr-fect! just the current team for now simplifies things a lot ",
          "providerMetadata": {
